Class TeaElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • tea.TeaElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext, org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.ISelect, org.openqa.selenium.TakesScreenshot, org.openqa.selenium.WebElement

    public class TeaElement
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.openqa.selenium.WebElement, org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.ISelect
    Tea element class wrapped web element class. If the wrapped element is Select object, ISelect interface is also available.

      • balloonAndWait

        public TeaElement balloonAndWait(java.lang.String message,
                                 java.lang.String properties,
                                 java.util.Map<java.lang.String,tea.MapValueObject> events)
        Pops up a balloon and wait for its disappearing. 
         
 // Display a balloon and wait until it is clicked to disappear.
 TeaElement te = 'Name'.balloonAndWait('Enter your name.', 'balloon:top;',
                 {onload: balloonElement -> moveElement(balloonElement, 200),
                  onhide: nextButton -> nextButton.click()});
        Parameters:
        message - the message to be displayed in balloon
        properties - the properties "key1:value1; key2:value2; ..."
        events - the Map object holding event functions (onload, onhide, onclick)
        Returns:
        the Tea element of the balloon

      • getValue

        public java.lang.Object getValue()
        Gets a value of this TeaElement. The value returned is determined based on the tag type. select tag with multiple attr: [SelectedOptionText1,Text2,...,TextN] select tag (single selection): A selected option text input tag: A value in the value attribute Others: The body text (if no body, a value in the value attribute)
        Returns:
        the value set in this TeaElement object.
